The '''Format Recognition and Protection Association''' ('''FRAPA''') is a [[trade association]] that seeks to create and enforce legal protection for [[television format]]s as [[intellectual property]], and to [[mediation|mediate]] industry disputes.<ref>{{Cite web|title=FRAPA official site|url=http://www.frapa.org/|accessdate=28 September 2010}}</ref>

FRAPA co-sponsors the [[C21 Media]] International Format Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|title=C21 Media International Format Awards|url=http://www.c21screenings.net/formatawards/|publisher=C21 Media|accessdate=28 September 2010}}</ref>

