{{Infobox song contest country |Name = Ukraine |Flag = Flag of Ukraine.svg |Member station = [[National Television Company of Ukraine|NTU]] |National selection event = National Selection |ESC apps = 2 |ESC first = [[Eurovision Dance Contest 2007|2007]] |ESC best = 2nd, [[Eurovision Dance Contest 2007|2007]] |ESC worst = 3rd, [[Eurovision Dance Contest 2008|2008]] |Website = {{cite web|url=http://esckaz.com/edc/2008/ukr.htm|title=Ukraine at Eurovision Dance Contest 2008}} |EBU page = http://www.eurovisiondance.tv/ua.php }}
[[Ukraine]] took part in the first [[Eurovision Dance Contest]] in 2007. Representing the country were [[Yulia Okropiridze]], a student of [[Kyiv National University of Culture and Arts]], and [[Illya Sydorenko]], a professional in ballroom choreography. The dances they performed on the night were [[Quickstep]] and [[Showdance]]. Ukraine came second after receiving 121 points from all other countries. Ukraine is arguably the most successful country to date, with two top 3 positions, despite not winning yet. [[Lilia Podkopayeva]] and [[Kirilo Hitrov]] represented the country in the [[Eurovision Dance Contest 2008|2008 contest]]. The [[Third Eurovision Dance Contest]] has been cancelled indefinitely.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=What caused the death of the Eurovision Dance Contest?|url=http://eurovoix.com/2011/05/29/what-caused-the-death-of-the-eurovision-dance-contest-p1/|website=Eurovoix.xom|publisher=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=22 June 2014|date=29 May 2011}}</ref>
